about Black culture will tell you; Black History stretches so far beyond 28 
days. Even though Black History Month is a great notion the way many of us 
approach Black History Month is pretty screwed up. If we’re not making fun 
of it or ignoring it outright, we recycle the same speeches on Rosa and 
Martin with a little Harriet Tubman or Malcolm every once in a while and a 
dash of Pres. Obama thrown in to show that we’re “post racial”. Black 
History Month has moved away from being a time where we learn about our 
history and just became something we have to do to be politically correct."> 
